🎮 Tetris Game in Python 🟦🟥🟩🟨
Welcome to the Tetris Game project! This is a simple implementation of the classic Tetris game using Python's pygame module. Perfect for beginners who want to level up their game development skills!

🌟 Features
✨ Key features of this project:

Classic Gameplay : Move, rotate, and drop blocks to clear lines. ⬇️🔄
Random Shapes : Includes all classic Tetris shapes (I, O, T, S, Z, L, J). 🔲
Line Clearing : Clear full rows to increase your score. 🏆
Simple Logic : Clean and beginner-friendly code. 💻
🛠️ Installation
Follow these steps to set up the game:

Install Python : Ensure you have Python 3.x installed. Download it from here . 🐍
Install Dependencies : Run the following command to install pygame:
bash
Copy
1
pip install pygame
Save the code into a file named app.py. 📂
▶️ Usage
Ready to play? Follow these steps:

Run the script:
bash
Copy
1
python app.py
Use the arrow keys to control the blocks:
Left Arrow : Move left. ⬅️
Right Arrow : Move right. ➡️
Down Arrow : Move down faster. ⬇️
Up Arrow : Rotate the block. 🔃
Clear lines to score points. 🏆
🔧 How It Works
⚙️ Quick overview of the game mechanics:

Grid Setup : The board is represented as a 2D grid. 🧮
Shapes : Randomly generated shapes fall from the top. 🔲
Collision Detection : Prevents blocks from overlapping or going out of bounds. 🚫
Line Clearing : Full rows are cleared, and the score increases. 🏆
🚀 Extending the Project
Here are some ideas to enhance the project:

Add Levels : Increase the speed as the score increases. ⏳
High Score Tracking : Save the highest score to a file. 📊
Custom Themes : Change colors or add animations for a personalized look. 🎨
Sound Effects : Add sound effects for block drops and line clears. 🔊
